{"parse":{"title":"Cognitive adequacy","pageid":53628878,"revid":782813050,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Cognitive adequacy</b> is a term proposed by <a href=\"/wiki/Rein_Raud\" title=\"Rein Raud\">Rein Raud</a> as a standard of judging <a href=\"/wiki/Bandwagon_effect\" title=\"Bandwagon effect\">cultural phenomena</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to this method, a cultural phenomenon is cognitively adequate if it provides the means of solving certain problems in a certain <a href=\"/wiki/Social_environment\" title=\"Social environment\">socio-cultural context</a>. This is true even when that solution is, according to other criteria, wrong. For example, before the <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Depression\" title=\"Great Depression\">Great Depression</a> in the US many people thought that it is cognitively adequate to think of getting rich quickly through <a href=\"/wiki/Land_speculation\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Land speculation\">land speculation</a>. All cultural phenomena are replaced by others when they are no longer cognitively adequate. For example, when a community has embraced a new religion, or when science has displaced religion as the primary explanatory discourse for their world.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Cognitive_adequacy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Raud, Rein (2016). <i>Meaning in Action: Outline of an Integral Theory of Culture</i>. Cambridge: Polity Books. pp.&#160;46\u201348. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781509511242\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781509511242\">9781509511242</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Meaning+in+Action%3A+Outline+of+an+Integral+Theory+of+Culture&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pages=46-48&amp;rft.pub=Polity+Books&amp;rft.date=2016&amp;rft.isbn=9781509511242&amp;rft.aulast=Raud&amp;rft.aufirst=Rein&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACognitive+adequacy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1332\nCached time: 20180909124221\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.060 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.076 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 47/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1360/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 3/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 1046/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.030/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1.33 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   62.759      1 Template:Cite_book\n100.00%   62.759      1 -total\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:53628878-0!canonical and timestamp 20180909124221 and revision id 782813050\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Culture"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Bandwagon effect"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Great Depression"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"International Standard Book Number"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Land speculation"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Rein Raud"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Social environmen